.TH "drm_helper_crtc_in_use" 9 "drm_helper_crtc_in_use" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_helper_crtc_in_use \- check if a given CRTC is in a mode_config
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_helper_crtc_in_use
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
CRTC to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether \fIcrtc\fP is with the current mode setting output configuration
in use by any connector. This doesn't mean that it is actually enabled since
the DPMS state is tracked separately.
.SH "RETURN"
True if \fIcrtc\fP is used, false otherwise.
